-- Hungary Misses Debt Auction Goal After IMF Suspends Talks With Government
-- Edith Balazs
-- 2010-07-20T09:32:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-20/hungary-misses-debt-auction-goal-after-imf-suspends-talks-with-government.html

          
          
             The Hungarian government raised 35
billion forint ($156 million), 10 billion forint less than
planned, at a sale of three-month Treasury bills today as debt
costs rose from the previous auction a week earlier.  
 The average yield on the auctioned maturity rose to 5.47
percent from 5.28 percent on July 13, according to auction
results on the debt management agencyâ€™s Bloomberg page.
Investors submitted bids worth 52.5 billion forint compared with
total bids of 102.5 billion a week earlier, the results showed.  
          
          


  


        